programme.title: Live Premier League
programme.sub-title: Tottenham Hotspur v West Ham United.
programme.desc: Tottenham Hotspur v West Ham United (Kick-off 8.00pm). Coverage of the top-flight encounter between the London rivals, which takes place at Wembley Stadium. These side last met on this ground back in October in the fourth round of the Carabao Cup, when the struggling Hammers pulled off a remarkable second-half fightback to win 3-2. Midfielders Moussa Sissoko and Dele Alli had given Spurs a seemingly comfortable half-time lead, but Andre Ayew's brace and a header from Angelo Ogbonna in the 70th minute sealed a stunning victory for manager Slaven Bilic, who was sacked less than a month later following a 4-1 home drubbing at the hands of Liverpool, being replaced by former Everton and Manchester United boss David Moyes. The home side won last season's corresponding fixture by the same scoreline of 3-2, with Harry Winks and a late double from Harry Kane sealing all three points for Mauricio Pochettino, after Michail Antonio and Manuel Lanzini had given the Hammers a 2-1 advantage with just minutes to go at White Hart Lane(n)

programme.title: Live PGA Tour Golf
programme.sub-title: 2018 Sentry Tournament of Champions: Day One.
programme.desc: The Sentry Tournament of Champions. Coverage of the first day's play of the tour's opening event of 2018, held at the Plantation Course at Kapalua in Hawaii. America's Justin Thomas won this tournament last year, finishing three strokes clear of Japan's Hideki Matsuyama to claim his third title on the tour, and further success was to follow in 2017 when he won the PGA Championship in August(n)

programme.desc: Tottenham Hotspur v West Ham United (Kick-off 8.00pm). Coverage of the top-flight encounter between the London rivals, which takes place at Wembley Stadium. These side last met on this ground back in October in the fourth round of the Carabao Cup, when the struggling Hammers pulled off a remarkable second-half fightback to win 3-2. Midfielders Moussa Sissoko and Dele Alli had given Spurs a seemingly comfortable half-time lead, but Andre Ayew's brace and a header from Angelo Ogbonna in the 70th minute sealed a stunning victory for manager Slaven Bilic, who was sacked less than a month later following a 4-1 home drubbing at the hands of Liverpool, being replaced by former Everton and Manchester United boss David Moyes. The home side won last season's corresponding fixture by the same scoreline of 3-2, with Harry Winks and a late double from Harry Kane sealing all three points for Mauricio Pochettino, after Michail Antonio and Manuel Lanzini had given the Hammers a 2-1 advantage with just minutes to go at White Hart Lane(n)
